{"title_page": "Avinash Kumar Agarwal", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Avinash Kumar Agarwal\n| image             = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1972|08|22}}\n| birth_place [[Karasuli, Rajasthan]], India\n| death_date        = \n| death_place       = \n| nationality       = [[Indian nationality|Indian]]\n| fields            = {{ublist | [[Mechanical engineering]] | [[Tribology]] }}\n| workplaces        = {{ublist | [[IIT Kanpur]] | [[Technical University of Vienna]] | [[University of Loughborough]] }}\n| alma_mater        = {{ublist | [[Malviya Regional Engineering College, Jaipur|MREC, Jaipur]] | [[IIT Delhi]] | [[University of Wisconsin, Madison, USA]] }}\n| doctoral_advisor  = {{ublist| L. M. Das }}\n| doctoral_students = \n| known_for         = Studies on [[internal combustion engines]] and [[Compressed natural gas|CNG]] engines, Laser diagnostics, Renewable Fuels e.g. Methanol, Emission Control.\n| awards            = {{ublist|2002&nbsp;[[Department of Science and Technology (India)|DST]] Young Scientist Award | 2004&nbsp;[[All India Council for Technical Education|AICTE]] Career Award | 2005&nbsp;[[Indian National Academy of Engineering|INAE]] Young Engineer Award | 2007&nbsp;[[Indian National Science Academy|INSA]] Young Scientists Medal | 2007&nbsp;[[Institute of Chemical Technology|UICT]] Alkyl Amine Young Scientist Award | 2008&nbsp;[[SAE International]] Ralph R. Teetor Educational Award | 2011&nbsp;[[IES Group of Institutions|IES]] C. V. Raman Young Teachers Award | 2012&nbsp;NASI-Reliance Industries Platinum Jubilee Award | 2012&nbsp;[[Indian National Academy of Engineering|INAE]] Silver Jubilee Young Engineer Award | 2016&nbsp;[[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize]] }}\n}}\n'''Avinash Kumar Agarwal''' (born 22 August 1972) is an Indian mechanical engineer, [[tribologist]] and a professor at the Department of Mechanical Engineering of the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur]].<ref name=\"Faculty profile\">{{Cite web |url=http://home.iitk.ac.in/~akag/ |title=Faculty profile |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> He is known for his studies on [[internal combustion engines]], [[Exhaust gas|Emissions]], [[alternate fuels]] and [[Compressed natural gas|CNG]] engines<ref name=\"Brief Profile of the Awardee\">{{Cite web |url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/Content/Detail.aspx?AID=516 |title=Brief Profile of the Awardee |date=2017 |publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize}}</ref> and is an elected fellow of the American Society of Mechanical Engineering (2013), Society of Automotive Engineers, USA (2012), National Academy of Science, Allahabad (2018), Royal Society of Chemistry, UK (2018), International Society for Energy, Environment and Sustainability (2016), and [[Indian National Academy of Engineering|Indian National Academy of Engineering (2015)]].<ref name=\"INAE fellows\">{{Cite web |url=https://inae.in/search-of-fellows/ |title=INAE fellows |date=2016 |publisher=Indian National Academy of Engineers |access-date=2017-02-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403030936/http://inae.in/search-of-fellows/ |archive-date=2015-04-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The [[Council of Scientific and Industrial Research]], the apex agency of the Government of India for scientific research, awarded him the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize for Science and Technology]], one of the highest Indian science awards for his contributions to Engineering Sciences in 2016.<ref name=\"View Bhatnagar Awardees\">{{cite web | url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/Content/AwardeeList.aspx | title=View Bhatnagar Awardees | publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize | date=2016 | accessdate=12 November 2016}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Long link - please select award year to see details}} Prof. Agarwal has recently been bestowed with Prestigious J C Bose Fellowship of Science and Engineering Research Board. Government of India (August 2019). Prof. Agarwal is among Top 10 highly cited researchers (HCR) of 2018 from India, as per Clarivate Analytics, an arm of Web of Science.\n\n== Biography ==\n[[File:IIT Kanpur Faculty Building.JPG|thumb|left|235px|IIT Kanpur]]\nAvinash Kumar Agarwal, born on 22 August 1972 at Karauli, in the Indian state of [[Rajasthan]], earned his graduate degree in mechanical engineering (BTech) from Malaviya Regional Engineering College (MREC) Jaipur (present-day [[Malaviya National Institute of Technology, Jaipur]]) of the [[University of Rajasthan]] in 1994 and did his master's degree at the Centre for Energy Studies of the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi]] from where he obtained an MTech in energy studies in 1996.<ref name=\"Education\">{{Cite web |url=http://home.iitk.ac.in/~akag/Education.htm |title=Education |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> immediately after this, he pursued his PhD at IIT Delhi,<ref name=\"Professional Experience\">{{Cite web |url=http://home.iitk.ac.in/~akag/Experience.htm |title=Professional Experience |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> in Center for energy studies, under the guidance of L. M. Das, which he successfully defended in 1999 for his thesis, ''Performance evaluation and tribological studies on a biodiesel-fuelled compression ignition engine''.<ref name=\"Performance evaluation and tribological studies on a biodiesel-fuelled compression ignition engine\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.eprint.iitd.ac.in/bitstream/2074/6452/1/TH-2661.pdf |title=Performance evaluation and tribological studies on a biodiesel-fuelled compression ignition engine |date=1996 |publisher=IIT Delhi}}</ref> Thereafter he moved to the US for his postdoctoral work which he completed at the Engine Research Center of the [[University of Wisconsin-Madison]] between 1999\u20132001. On his return to India in March 2001, he joined the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur]] as an assistant professor.<ref name=\"Agarwal on INAE\">{{Cite web |url=https://inae.in/expert-search/index.php/avinashkumar-agarwal |title=Agarwal on INAE |date=2017 |publisher=Indian National Academy of Engineering}}</ref> He was promoted as an associate professor in 2007 and has been serving the institute since 2012 as a professor at the Department of Mechanical Engineering.<ref name=\"Professor, Department of Mechanical Engineering\">{{Cite web |url=http://iitk.ac.in/new/avinash-kumar-agarwal |title=Professor, Department of Mechanical Engineering |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> He had seven short stints abroad as visiting professor during this period, first at Wolfson School of Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering of the [[University of Loughborough]] in 2002 second and third, at Photonics Institute of [[Technical University of Vienna]] in 2004 and 2013, and the fourth, fifth and sixth at Hanyang University, South Korea in 2013, 2014 and 2015 and the last stint at Korea Advanced Institute of Science and Technology (KAIST) in 2016.<ref name=\"Professional Experience\" />\n\nAgarwal is married to Dr. Rashmi A. Agarwal and the couple has two children, Aditya (b. 2003) and Rithwik (b. 2006).<ref name=\"Personal Profile\">{{Cite web |url=http://home.iitk.ac.in/~akag/Personal.htm |title=Personal Profile |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> The family lives in Kanpur in [[Uttar Pradesh]].<ref name=\"Faculty profile\" />\n\n== Legacy ==\n[[File:Four stroke engine diagram.jpg|thumb|235px|Four stroke engine diagram]]\nAgrawal's researches has covered the fields of engine combustion, alternate fuels, emission and particulate control, optical diagnosis, Methanol Engine Development, fuel spray optimization and [[tribology]] and his work has assisted in the development of low-cost diesel oxidation catalysts and [[homogeneous charge compression ignition]] engines.<ref name=\"Brief Profile of the Awardee\" /> His studies of laser ignition of methane-air hydrogen-air mixtures and [[biodiesel]] based on Indian [[feedstock]]s have widened the understanding of the subjects;<ref name=\"Agarwal on INAE\" /> he carried out a project on biodiesels during 2010\u201313 for the [[Department of Science and Technology (India)|Department of Science and Technology of India]].<ref name=\"Project Summary\">{{Cite web |url=http://dst.gov.in/sites/default/files/7Avinash%20Kumar%20Agarwal.pdf |title=Project Summary |date=2017 |publisher=Department of Science and Technology}}</ref> He has documented his researches by way of over 280 articles;<ref name=\"On Thermal Science\">{{Cite web |url=http://thermalscience.vinca.rs/authors/1698 |title=On Thermal Science |date=2017 |publisher=Thermal Science journal}}</ref><ref name=\"On SAE International\">{{Cite web |url=http://profiles.sae.org/avinash_kumar_agarwal/ |title=On SAE International |date=2017 |publisher=SAE International}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Please see ''Articles'' section}} [[Google Scholar]] and [[ResearchGate]], online repositories of scientific articles, have listed many of them.<ref name=\"On Google Scholar\">{{Cite web |url=https://scholar.google.co.in/citations?user=cGOyLQsAAAAJ |title=On Google Scholar |date=2016 |publisher=Google Scholar}}</ref><ref name=\"On ResearchGate\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Avinash_Agarwal4 |title=On ResearchGate |date=2016 |publisher=On ResearchGate}}</ref> Besides, he has edited forty books, most of which are published by Springer, including, ''Combustion for Power Generation and Transportation'',<ref name=\"Combustion for Power Generation and Transportation\">{{Cite book |url=https://www.springer.com/gp/book/9789811037849#aboutAuthors |title=Combustion for Power Generation and Transportation |author=Agarwal, A.K. |author2=De, S. |author3=Pandey, A. |author4=Singh, A.P. |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-981-10-3784-9 |page=451|year=2017 }}</ref> and ''Novel Combustion Concepts for Sustainable Energy Development''<ref name=\"Novel Combustion Concepts for Sustainable Energy Development\">{{Cite book |url=https://www.springer.com/gp/book/9788132222101 |title=Novel Combustion Concepts for Sustainable Energy Development |author=Agarwal, A.K. |author2=Pandey, A. |author3=Gupta, A.K. |author4=Aggarwal, S.K. |author5=Kushari, A. |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-81-322-2211-8 |date=2014 |page=562}}</ref> and has contributed forty two chapters to many books.<ref name=\"AgarwalDe2017\">{{cite book|author1=Avinash Kumar Agarwal|author2=Santanu De|author3=Ashok Pandey, Akhilendra Pratap Singh|title=Combustion for Power Generation and Transportation: Technology, Challenges and Prospects|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pGELDgAAQBAJ&pg=PR8|date=29 March 2017|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-981-10-3785-6|pages=8\u2013}}</ref> He is also a co-editor of a five-volume reference text, ''Handbook of Combustion'', published by Wiley-VCH in 2010.<ref name=\"Handbook of Combustion\">{{Cite book |url=http://eu.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-3527324496.html |title=Handbook of Combustion |editor=Maximilian Lackner |editor2=Franz Winter |editor3=Avinash K. Agarwal |publisher=Wiley-VCH |isbn=978-3-527-32449-1 |date=April 2010 |page=3168}}</ref>\n\nAgarwal is the Associate Principle Editor of Journal \"Fuel\", Editor-in-chief of Journal of Energy and Environmental Sustainability (JEES)<ref name=\"Editor in chief\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.jees.in/editorial.html |title=Editor in chief |date=2017 |publisher=Journal of Energy and Environmental Sustainability |access-date=12 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170212164535/http://www.jees.in/editorial.html |archive-date=12 February 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and is Associate Editor of two other journals, \"ASME Journal of Energy Resources Technology\", and \"Journal of the Institution of Engineers (India): Series C\". He is a member of the editorial board of several prestigious journals such as \"International Journal of Engine Research, published by SAE International and IMechE, London, UK\", ''Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D: Journal of Automobile Engineering''<ref name=\"Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D: Journal of Automobile Engineering\">{{Cite web |url=https://us.sagepub.com/en-us/nam/journal/proceedings-institution-mechanical-engineers-part-d-journal-automobile-engineering#editorial-board |title=Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D: Journal of Automobile Engineering |date=2017 |publisher=Sage Publications}}</ref> and ''Recent Patents on Mechanical Engineering'' of [[Bentham Science]].<ref name=\"Editorial Board Members RPME\">{{Cite web |url=http://benthamscience.com/journals/recent-patents-on-mechanical-engineering/editorial-board/#top |title=Editorial Board Members RPME |date=2017 |publisher=Bentham Science}}</ref> He is also a former associate editor of the ''International Journal of Vehicle Systems Modelling and Testing'' of [[Inderscience Publishers]], \"International Journal of Oil, Gas and Coal Technology\" (IJOGCT), Published by Inderscience Publishers and guest-edited a special issue of the Journal of Automobile Engineering on ''Alternative Fuels'' in 2007.<ref name=\"Table of Contents\">{{Cite web |url=http://journals.sagepub.com/toc/pidb/221/8 |title=Table of Contents |date=2017 |publisher=Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D}}</ref> He is a member of the Methanol Task Force of the Department of Science and Technology since 2017, former member of Technology Systems Group of the Department of Science and Technology and a former member of the Experts Group on ''Biofuels and Retrofitting of Engines'' of the Government of India.<ref name=\"Engine Research Laboratory Awards\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.iitk.ac.in/erl/Awards.htm |title=Engine Research Laboratory Awards |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> He is a member of the board of associates of the Internal Combustion Engines Division of American Society of Mechanical Engineering and is associated with [[SAE International]], sitting in many of their review committees.\nHe was the session organizer for 2005, 2006, 2007, 2008 and 2009 editions of SAE World Congress and chaired the 2004, 2005 and 2006 sessions on alternative fuel and internal combustion engines.<ref name=\"Engine Research Laboratory Awards\" />\n\n== Awards and honors ==\nAgarwal received the Young Scientist Award of the [[Department of Science and Technology (India)|Department of Science and Technology]] in 2002, followed by the Career Award for Young Teachers of the [[All India Council of Technical Education]] (AICTE) in 2004.<ref name=\"ResearchGate profile\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Avinash_Agarwal4/info |title=ResearchGate profile |date=2017 |publisher=ResearchGate}}</ref> The Young Engineer Award of the [[Indian National Academy of Engineering]] reached him in 2005<ref name=\"INAE Young Engineer Award\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.csir.res.in/External/Heads/aboutcsir/announcements/young_engineer.html |title=INAE Young Engineer Award |date=2017 |publisher=Council of Scientific and Industrial Research |access-date=12 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323181922/http://www.csir.res.in/External/Heads/aboutcsir/announcements/young_engineer.html |archive-date=23 March 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and the Young Scientists Medal of the [[Indian National Science Academy]] came his way in 2007.<ref name=\"INSA Young Scientists Medal\">{{Cite web |url=http://insaindia.res.in/youngmedal.php |title=INSA Young Scientists Medal |date=2016 |publisher=Indian National Science Academy}}</ref> He received the Alkyl Amine Young Scientist Award of the [[Institute of Chemical Technology]] the same year and a year later, [[SAE International]] selected him for the 2008 Ralph R. Teetor Educational Award.<ref name=\"Ten Engineering Educators Receive SAE Award\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.sae.org/news/830/ |title=Ten Engineering Educators Receive SAE Award |date=7 July 2008 |publisher=SAE International |access-date=12 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170213000556/https://www.sae.org/news/830/ |archive-date=13 February 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He received the C. V. Raman Young Teachers Award of the [[IES Group of Institutions|IES Group]] in 2011 and NASI-[[Reliance Industries]] Platinum Jubilee Award of the [[National Academy of Sciences, India]] in 2012.<ref name=\"NASI-Reliance Industries Platinum Jubilee Award\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nasi.org.in/ripja.htm |title=NASI-Reliance Industries Platinum Jubilee Award |date=2017 |publisher=National Academy of Sciences, India}}</ref> The Indian National Academy of Engineering honored him again in 2012 with the Silver Jubilee Young Engineer Award, which was followed by \"Rajib Goyal Prize\" in Physical Sciences-2015 from Kurukshetra University and then [[Council of Scientific and Industrial Research]] awarded him the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize]], one of the highest Indian science awards in 2016.<ref name=\"Engineering Sciences\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.csir.res.in/external/heads/career/award/BPRIZE/Engineering_SCIENCES.htm |title=Engineering Sciences |date=2016 |publisher=Council of Scientific and Industrial Research |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923211647/http://www.csir.res.in/external/heads/career/award/BPRIZE/Engineering_SCIENCES.htm |archivedate=23 September 2015 }}</ref> Afterwards, he was conferred \"Er. M P Baya National Award-2017\" in Mechanical Engineering by Institution of Engineers, Udaipur and Clarivate Analytics India Research Excellence - Citation Award-2017, which was 6th Edition prize for high citations and high impact work from India, given by Clarivate Analytics.\n\nAgarwal, who held the BOYSCAST Fellowship of Department of Science and Technology in 2002 and Devendra Shukla Research Fellowship of IIT Kanpur in 2009, was elected as a fellow by the Indian National Academy of Engineering in 2015.<ref name=\"Agarwal on INAE\" /> He is also a fellow of the [[American Society of Mechanical Engineers]] and [[SAE International]], Royal Society of Chemistry, Indian National Academy of Engineering, National Academy of Sciences and International Society for Energy, Environment and Sustainability<ref name=\"Engine Research Laboratory Awards\" /> He was listed in several editions of [[Marquis Who's Who]] in Science and Engineering, Who's Who (Emerging Leaders) and Who's Who in the World.<ref name=\"Engine Research Laboratory Awards\" /> Agarwal was Poonam and Prabhu Goyal Chair Professor at IIT Kanpur from 2012\u201316. He is currently SBI Endowed chair Professor in the same institution (2018-2021).\n\n== Selected bibliography ==\n=== Books ===\n* Environmental Contaminants, 431 pages, Published by Springer, Singapore (2018), (Eds.) Tarun Gupta, Avinash K Agarwal, Rashmi A Agarwal, Nitin K Labhsetwar ({{ISBN|978-981-10-7332-8}}) DOI: 10.1007/978-981-10-7332-8.\n* Air Pollution and Control, 260 pages, Published by Springer, Singapore (2018), (Eds.) Nikhil Sharma, Avinash K Agarwal, Peter Eastwood, Tarun Gupta, Akhilendra P Singh ({{ISBN|978-981-10-7184-3}}) DOI: 10.1007/978-981-10-7185-0.\n* Coal and Biomass Gasification, 521 pages, Published by Springer, Singapore (2018), (Eds.) Santanu De, Avinash K Agarwal, V S Moholkar, Thallada Bhaskar ({{ISBN|978-981-10-7334-2}}) DOI: 10.1007/978-981-10-7335-9.\n* Droplets and Sprays, 430 pages, Published by Springer, Singapore (2018), (Eds.) Saptarshi Basu, Avinash K Agarwal, Achintya Mukhopadhyay, Chetan Patel ({{ISBN|978-981-10-7448-6}}) DOI: 10.1007/978-981-10-7449-3.\n* Advances in Internal Combustion Engine Research, 345 pages, Published by Springer, Singapore (2018), (Eds.) Dhananjay K Srivastava, Avinash K Agarwal, Amitava Datta, Rakesh K Maurya ({{ISBN|978-981-10-7574-2}}) DOI: 10.1007/978-981-10-7575-9.\n* Modeling and Simulations of Turbulent Combustion, 661 pages, Published