1-10-3788-7.\n* Biofuels: Technology, Challenges and Prospects, 245 pages, Published by Springer, Singapore (2017), (Eds.) Avinash Kumar Agarwal, Rashmi Avinash Agarwal, Tarun Gupta, Bhola Ram Gurjar. DOI: 10-1007/978-981-10-3791-7 ({{ISBN|978-981-10-3790-0}}). DOI: 10.1007/978-981-10-3791-7.\n* Technology Vision 2015: Technology Roadmap Transportation, 237 pages, (Eds.) Avinash Kumar Agarwal, S S Thipse, Akhilendra P Singh, Gautam Goswami, Mukti Prasad, Published by TIFAC, New Delhi, December 2016.\n* Energy, Combustion and Propulsion: New Perspectives, 609 pages, Published by Athena Academic, London, UK (2016), (Eds.) Avinash K Agarwal, Suresh K. Aggarwal, Ashwani K. Gupta, Abhijit Kushari, Ashok Pandey ({{ISBN|978-19-1039-029-0}})\n* Novel Combustion Concepts for Sustainable Energy Development, 562 pages, Published by Springer, Singapore (2014), (Eds.) Avinash K. Agarwal, Ashok Pandey, Ashwani K. Gupta, Suresh K. Aggarwal, Abhijit Kushari. ({{ISBN|978-81-322-2210-1}}). DOI: 10.1007/978-81-322-2211-8-18.\n* ''Handbook of Combustion'', 5 Volumes, 3168 pages, Hardcover, April 2010, Published by Wiley VCH, (Eds.) Maximilian Lackner, Franz Winter, Avinash K. Agarwal ({{ISBN|978-3-527-32449-1}}).\n* ''CI Engine Performance for Use with Alternative Fuels, 2009(SP-2237)'', 185 pages, Published by SAE International, USA, 2009, (Eds.) Amiyo K Basu, Avinash Kumar Agarwal, Paul Richards, G. J. Thompson, Scott A Miers, Sundar Rajan Krishnan ({{ISBN|978-0-7680-2133-2}}).\n* ''Combustion Science and Technology: Recent Trends'' Published by Narosa Publishing House, New Delhi, 2009 (Eds.) A. K. Agarwal, A. Kushari, S. K. Aggarwal, A. K. Runchal, 300 Pages ({{ISBN|978-81-8487-014-5}}). \n* ''CI Engine Performance for use with Alternative Fuels (SP-2176)'', Published by SAE International, USA, 2008, (Eds.) Avinash K. Agarwal, G. J. Thompson, Scott A. Miers, Sundar R. Krishnan ({{ISBN|978-0-7680-2018-2}}).\n* ''Alternative Fuels and CI Engine Performance (SP-2067)'', 160 Pages, Published by SAE International, USA, 2007, (Eds.) Avinash K. Agarwal, G. J. Thompson ({{ISBN|978-0-7680-1857-8}}). \n* ''New Diesel Engines and Components and CI Engine performance for Use with Alternative Fuels (SP-2014)'', 171 Pages, Published by SAE International, USA, 2006, (Eds.) A. Jain, J. E. Mossberg, Avinash K. Agarwal, G. J. Thompson ({{ISBN|0-7680-1749-1}}).\n* ''CI Engine performance for Use with Alternative Fuels, and New Diesel Engines and Components (SP-1978)'', 196 Pages, Published by SAE International, USA, 2005, (Eds.) J. E. Mossberg, A. Jain, G. J. Thompson, Avinash K. Agarwal ({{ISBN|0-7680-1623-1}}).\n\n=== Articles ===\n* Avinash K Agarwal*, Bushra Ateeq, Tarun Gupta, Akhilendra P. Singh, Swaroop K Pandey, Nikhil Sharma, Rashmi A Agarwal, Neeraj K. Gupta, Hemant Sharma, Ayush Jain, Pravesh C Shukla, \"Toxicity and mutagenicity of exhaust from compressed natural gas: Could this be a clean solution for megacities with mixed-traffic conditions?\u201d, Environmental Pollution. 239, 499\u2013511, 2018.doi: 10.1016/j.envpol.2018.04.028 \n* {{Cite journal |last=Avinash Kumar Agarwal |title=Biofuels (alcohols and biodiesel) applications as fuels for internal combustion engines |journal=Progress in Energy and Combustion Science |date=2007 |volume=33 |issue=3 |pages=233\u2013271 |doi=10.1016/j.pecs.2006.08.003}}\n* {{Cite journal |author=Deepak Agarwal |author2=Lokesh Kumar |author3=Avinash Kumar Agarwal |title=Performance evaluation of a vegetable oil fuelled compression ignition engine |journal=Renewable Energy |date=2008 |volume=33 |issue=6 |pages=1147\u20131156 |doi=10.1016/j.renene.2007.06.017}}\n* {{Cite journal |last=Avinash Kumar Agarwal, K. Rajamanoharan |title=Experimental investigations of performance and emissions of Karanja oil and its blends in a single cylinder agricultural diesel engine |journal=Applied Energy |date=2009 |volume=86 |issue=1 |pages=106\u2013112 |doi=10.1016/j.apenergy.2008.04.008}}\n* {{Cite journal |author=Joonsik Hwang |author2=Choongsik Bae |author3=Chetankumar Patel |author4=Avinash Kumar Agarwal |title=An Experimental Investigation on Spray Characteristics of Waste Cooking Oil, Jatropha, and Karanja Biodiesels in a Constant Volume Combustion Chamber |journal=SAE International Technical Papers |volume=1 |date=2016 |doi=10.4271/2016-01-2263|series=SAE Technical Paper Series }}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Diesel fuel]]\n* [[Vegetable oil]]\n{{portal|India|Engineering}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{Cite web |last= Avinash Kumar Agrawal|url=http://www.eprint.iitd.ac.in/bitstream/2074/6452/1/TH-2661.pdf |title=Performance evaluation and tribological studies on a biodiesel-fuelled compression ignition engine |date=1996 |publisher=IIT Delhi |work=Doctoral thesis}}\n* {{Cite web |title=Alternative Fuels |last=Avinash K. Agarwal |publisher=Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D volume 221 issue 8 |date=2007 |work=Guest editorial}}\n\n{{SSBPST recipients in Engineering Science}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Agarwal, Avinash Kumar}}\n[[Category:Recipients of the Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Award in Engineering Science]]\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Indian technology writers]]\n[[Category:People from Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Indian mechanical engineers]]\n[[Category:Tribologists]]\n[[Category:University of Rajasthan alumni]]\n[[Category:Indian Institute of Technology Delhi alumni]]\n[[Category:Indian Institute of Technology Delhi faculty]]\n[[Category:Indian Institute of Technology Kanpur faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Wisconsin\u2013Madison alumni]]\n[[Category:Academics of Loughborough University]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Indian National Academy of Engineering]]\n", "text_old": "<gallery>\n</gallery>\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Prof. Avinash Kumar Agarwal\n| image             = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1972|08|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Karauli, Rajasthan]], India\n| death_date        = \n| death_place       = \n| nationality       = [[Indian nationality|Indian]]\n| fields            = {{ublist | [[Mechanical engineering]] | [[Tribology]] }}\n| workplaces        = {{ublist | [[IIT Kanpur]] | [[Technical University of Vienna]] | [[University of Loughborough]] }}\n| alma_mater        = {{ublist | [[Malviya Regional Engineering College, Jaipur|MREC, Jaipur]] | [[IIT Delhi]] | [[Engine Research Center, UW, Madison, USA]] }}\n| doctoral_advisor  = {{ublist| Prof. L. M. Das }}\n| doctoral_students = \n| known_for         = Studies on [[internal combustion engines]] and [[Methanol, and Compressed natural gas|CNG]] engines, Laser Ignition and Optical diagnostics, Coventional and Renewable Fuels, Gaseous Emissions and Particulate Control, Low Temperature Combustion, IC Engine Modeling and Simulations, Lubricating Oil Tribology.\n| awards            = {{ublist|2002&nbsp;[[Department of Science and Technology (India)|DST]] Young Scientist Award | 2004&nbsp;[[All India Council for Technical Education|AICTE]] Career Award | 2005&nbsp;[[Indian National Academy of Engineering|INAE]] Young Engineer Award | 2007&nbsp;[[Indian National Science Academy|INSA]] Young Scientists Medal | 2007&nbsp;[[Institute of Chemical Technology|UICT]] Alkyl Amine Young Scientist Award | 2008&nbsp;[[SAE International]] Ralph R. Teetor Educational Award | 2009&nbsp;[[Indian Institute of Technology Kanpur|IIT Kanpur]] Devendra Shukla Research Fellowship | 2011&nbsp;[[IES Group of Institutions|IES]] C. V. Raman Young Teachers Award | 2012&nbsp;NASI-Reliance Industries Platinum Jubilee Award | 2012&nbsp;[[Indian National Academy of Engineering|INAE]] Silver Jubilee Young Engineer Award | 2013&nbsp;[[Indian Institute of Technology Kanpur|IIT Kanpur]] Poonam and Prabhu Goyal Endowed Chair Professor | 2015&nbsp;[Kurukshetra University] Rajib Goyal Prize in Physical Sciences | 2016&nbsp;[[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize]] | 2017&nbsp;[[Institution of Engineers|IE(I)]] Er. M P Baya National Award in Mechanical Engineering | 2017&nbsp;[[Clarivate Analytics]] India Research Excellence - Citation Laureate Award | 2018&nbsp;[[IIT Kanpur]] State Bank of India Endowed Chair Professor }} \n}} \n\n\n'''Avinash Kumar Agarwal''' (born 22 August 1972) is an Indian mechanical engineer, and a professor at the Department of Mechanical Engineering of the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur]].<ref name=\"Faculty profile\">{{Cite web |url=http://home.iitk.ac.in/~akag/ |title=Faculty profile |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> He is known for his studies on [[internal combustion engines]], [[Exhaust gas|Emissions]], [[alternate fuels]] and [[Compressed natural gas|CNG]] engines<ref name=\"Brief Profile of the Awardee\">{{Cite web |url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/Content/Detail.aspx?AID=516 |title=Brief Profile of the Awardee |date=2017 |publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize}}</ref> and is an elected fellow of the American Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS-2019), National Academy of Science, Allahabad (NASI-2018), Royal Society of Chemistry, UK (RSC-2018), International Society for Energy, Environment and Sustainability (ISEES-2016), [[Indian National Academy of Engineering|Indian National Academy of Engineering (INAE-2015)<ref name=\"INAE fellows\">{{Cite web |url=https://inae.in/search-of-fellows/ |title=INAE fellows |date=2016 |publisher=Indian National Academy of Engineers |access-date=2017-02-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403030936/http://inae.in/search-of-fellows/}}</ref>, American Society of Mechanical Engineering (ASME-2013), and Society of Automotive Engineers International, USA (SAE-2012)]][[Avinash Kumar Agarwal#cite%20note-INAE%20fellows-3|<span class=\"mw-reflink-text\">[3]</span>]], American Society of Mechanical Engineering (ASME-2013), and Society of Automotive Engineers International, USA (SAE-2012)[[Avinash Kumar Agarwal#cite%20note-INAE%20fellows-3|<span class=\"mw-reflink-text\">[3]</span>]], American Society of Mechanical Engineering (ASME-2013), and Society of Automotive Engineers International, USA (SAE-2012)[[Avinash Kumar Agarwal#cite%20note-INAE%20fellows-3|<span class=\"mw-reflink-text\">[3]</span>]], American Society of Mechanical Engineering (ASME-2013), and Society of Automotive Engineers International, USA (SAE-2012). The [[Council of Scientific and Industrial Research]], the apex agency of the Government of India for scientific research, awarded him the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize for Science and Technology]], one of the highest Indian science awards for his contributions to Engineering Sciences in 2016.<ref name=\"View Bhatnagar Awardees\">{{cite web | url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/Content/AwardeeList.aspx | title=View Bhatnagar Awardees | publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize | date=2016 | accessdate=12 November 2016}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Long link - please select award year to see details}} Prof. Agarwal has recently been bestowed with Prestigious J C Bose Fellowship of Science and Engineering Research Board. Government of India (August 2019). Prof. Agarwal is among Top 10 highly cited researchers (HCR) of 2018 from India, as per Clarivate Analytics, an arm of Web of Science.\n\n== Biography ==\n[[File:IIT Kanpur Faculty Building.JPG|thumb|left|235px|IIT Kanpur]]\nAvinash Kumar Agarwal, born on 22 August 1972 at Karauli, in the Indian state of [[Rajasthan]], earned his undergraduate degree in Mechanical Engineering (B.E.) from Malaviya Regional Engineering College (MREC) Jaipur (present-day [[Malaviya National Institute of Technology, Jaipur]]) of the [[University of Rajasthan]] in 1994 and then obtained gradaute degrees (M.Tech. and Ph.D) from the Center for Energy Studies of the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi]] in the specializations in energy studies  and IC Engines in 1996 and 1999 respectively.<ref name=\"Education\">{{Cite web |url=http://home.iitk.ac.in/~akag/Education.htm |title=Education |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> His PhD at IIT Delhi,<ref name=\"Professional Experience\">{{Cite web |url=http://home.iitk.ac.in/~akag/Experience.htm |title=Professional Experience |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> in Center for energy studies, was under the guidance of Prof. L. M. Das, and his thesis topic was, ''Performance evaluation and tribological studies on a biodiesel-fuelled compression ignition engine''.<ref name=\"Performance evaluation and tribological studies on a biodiesel-fuelled compression ignition engine\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.eprint.iitd.ac.in/bitstream/2074/6452/1/TH-2661.pdf |title=Performance evaluation and tribological studies on a biodiesel-fuelled compression ignition engine |date=1996 |publisher=IIT Delhi}}</ref> Thereafter he moved to the US for his postdoctoral research at the Engine Research Center of the [[University of Wisconsin-Madison]] between 1999\u20132001. On his return to India in March 2001, he joined the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur]] as an Assistant Professor.<ref name=\"Agarwal on INAE\">{{Cite web |url=https://inae.in/expert-search/index.php/avinashkumar-agarwal |title=Agarwal on INAE |date=2017 |publisher=Indian National Academy of Engineering}}</ref> He was promoted to be an Asociate Professor in 2007 and he has been serving the institute since 2012 as a Professor at the Department of Mechanical Engineering.<ref name=\"Professor, Department of Mechanical Engineering\">{{Cite web |url=http://iitk.ac.in/new/avinash-kumar-agarwal |title=Professor, Department of Mechanical Engineering |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> He had several short stints abroad as visiting professor during this period, first at Wolfson School of Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering of the [[University of Loughborough]] in 2002, at Photonics Institute of [[Technical University of Vienna]] in 2004 and 2013, and then at Hanyang University, South Korea in 2013, 2014 and 2015, followed by a stint at Korea Advanced Institute of Science and Technology (KAIST) in 2016.<ref name=\"Professional Experience\" />\n\nAgarwal is married to Dr. Rashmi A. Agarwal and the couple has two children, Aditya (b. 2003) and Rithwik (b. 2006).<ref name=\"Personal Profile\">{{Cite web |url=http://home.iitk.ac.in/~akag/Personal.htm |title=Personal Profile |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> The family lives in Kanpur in [[Uttar Pradesh]].<ref name=\"Faculty profile\" />\n\n\n\n== Legacy ==\n[[File:Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Award being bestowed by Sh. Narendra Modi, Hon, Prime Minister of India.jpg|alt=|thumb|235x235px|Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Award being bestowed by Sh. Narendra Modi, Hon, Prime Minister of India (February 2019)]]\nProf. Agrawal's research has covered the fields of internal combustion engines, alternate fuels, gaseous emissions and particulate control, laser ignition, optical diagnostics, Methanol and DME engine development, fuel spray visualisation, characterisation and optimization, lubricating oil [[tribology]] etc. His work has assisted in the development of low-cost diesel oxidation catalysts, Methanol and DME fuelled prototype vehicles and [[homogeneous charge compression ignition]] engines.<ref name=\"Brief Profile of the Awardee\" /> His studies of laser ignition of methane-air hydrogen-air mixtures and [[biodiesel]] based on Indian [[feedstock]]s have widened the understanding of the subjects;<ref name=\"Agarwal on INAE\" /> he carried out a project on biodiesel during 2010\u201313 for the [[Department of Science and Technology (India)|Department of Science and Technology of India]].<ref name=\"Project Summary\">{{Cite web |url=http://dst.gov.in/sites/default/files/7Avinash%20Kumar%20Agarwal.pdf |title=Project Summary |date=2017 |publisher=Department of Science and Technology}}</ref> He has documented his researches by way of over 280+ articles;<ref name=\"On Thermal Science\">{{Cite web |url=http://thermalscience.vinca.rs/authors/1698 |title=On Thermal Science |date=2017 |publisher=Thermal Science journal}}</ref><ref name=\"On SAE International\">{{Cite web |url=http://profiles.sae.org/avinash_kumar_agarwal/ |title=On SAE International |date=2017 |publisher=SAE International}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Please see ''Articles'' section}} [[Google Scholar]] and [[ResearchGate]], online repositories of scientific articles, have listed many of them.<ref name=\"On Google Scholar\">{{Cite web |url=https://scholar.google.co.in/citations?user=cGOyLQsAAAAJ |title=On Google Scholar |date=2016 |publisher=Google Scholar}}</ref><ref name=\"On ResearchGate\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Avinash_Agarwal4 |title=On ResearchGate |date=2016 |publisher=On ResearchGate}}</ref> Besides, he has edited forty five books, most of which are published by Springer, including, ''Combustion for Power Generation and Transportation'',<ref name=\"Combustion for Power Generation and Transportation\">{{Cite book |url=https://www.springer.com/gp/book/9789811037849#aboutAuthors |title=Combustion for Power Generation and Transportation |author=Agarwal, A.K. |author2=De, S. |author3=Pandey, A. |author4=Singh, A.P. |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-981-10-3784-9 |page=451|year=2017 }}</ref> and ''Novel Combustion Concepts for Sustainable Energy Development''<ref name=\"Novel Combustion Concepts for Sustainable Energy Development\">{{Cite book |url=https://www.springer.com/gp/book/9788132222101 |title=Novel Combustion Concepts for Sustainable Energy Development |author=Agarwal, A.K. |author2=Pandey, A. |author3=Gupta, A.K. |author4=Aggarwal, S.K. |author5=Kushari, A. |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-81-322-2211-8 |date=2014 |page=562}}</ref> and has contributed sixty five chapters to many books.<ref name=\"AgarwalDe2017\">{{cite book|author1=Avinash Kumar Agarwal|author2=Santanu De|author3=Ashok Pandey, Akhilendra Pratap Singh|title=Combustion for Power Generation and Transportation: Technology, Challenges and Prospects|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pGELDgAAQBAJ&pg=PR8|date=29 March 2017|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-981-10-3785-6|pages=8\u2013}}</ref> He is also a co-editor of a five-volume reference text, ''Handbook of Combustion'', published by Wiley-VCH in 2010.<ref name=\"Handbook of Combustion\">{{Cite book |url=http://eu.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-3527324496.html |title=Handbook of Combustion |editor=Maximilian Lackner |editor2=Franz Winter |editor3=Avinash K. Agarwal |publisher=Wiley-VCH |isbn=978-3-527-32449-1 |date=April 2010 |page=3168}}</ref>\n\nProf. Agarwal is the Associate Principle Editor of Journal \"Fuel\", Editor-in-chief of Journal of Energy and Environmental Sustainability (JEES)<ref name=\"Editor in chief\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.jees.in/editorial.html |title=Editor in chief |date=2017 |publisher=Journal of Energy and Environmental Sustainability |access-date=12 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170212164535/http://www.jees.in/editorial.html |archive-date=12 February 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and is Associate Editor of \"Journal of the Institution of Engineers (India): Series C\". He is a member of the editorial board of several prestigious journals such as \"International Journal of Engine Research, published by SAE International and IMechE, London, UK\", ''Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D: Journal of Automobile Engineering''<ref name=\"Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D: Journal of Automobile Engineering\">{{Cite web |url=https://us.sagepub.com/en-us/nam/journal/proceedings-institution-mechanical-engineers-part-d-journal-automobile-engineering#editorial-board |title=Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D: Journal of Automobile Engineering |date=2017 |publisher=Sage Publications}}</ref> and ''Recent Patents on Mechanical Engineering'' of [[Bentham Science]].<ref name=\"Editorial Board Members RPME\">{{Cite web |url=http://benthamscience.com/journals/recent-patents-on-mechanical-engineering/editorial-board/#top |title=Editorial Board Members RPME |date=2017 |publisher=Bentham Science}}</ref> He is also a former associate editor of the ASME Journal of Energy Resources Technology, ''International Journal of Vehicle Systems Modelling and Testing'' of [[Inderscience Publishers]], International Journal of Oil, Gas and Coal Technology (IJOGCT), Published by Inderscience Publishers and guest-editor of a special issue of the Journal of Automobile Engineering on ''Alternative Fuels'', published in 2007.<ref name=\"Table of Contents\">{{Cite web |url=http://journals.sagepub.com/toc/pidb/221/8 |title=Table of Contents |date=2017 |publisher=Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D}}</ref> He is a member of the Methanol Task Force of the Department of Science and Technology since 2017, member of the Methanol Task Force of the NITI Ayog since 2018, former member of Technology Systems Group of the Department of Science and Technology and a former member of the Experts Group on ''Biofuels and Retrofitting of Engines'' of the Government of India.<ref name=\"Engine Research Laboratory Awards\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.iitk.ac.in/erl/Awards.htm |title=Engine Research Laboratory Awards |date=2017 |publisher=IIT Kanpur}}</ref> He is the Chair of CPCB Sub-committee for developing Locomotive Emission Norms for India since 2019. He is a member of CPCB Standing Committee on Emissions for Off-Road Applications since 2018. He is a member of the board of associates of the Internal Combustion Engines Division of American Society of Mechanical Engineering since 2005 and is associated with [[SAE International]], sitting in many of their review committees.\nHe was the session organizer for 2005, 2006, 2007, 2008 and 2009 editions of SAE World Congress and chaired the 2004, 2005 and 2006 sessions on alternative fuel and internal combustion engines in ASME-ICED conferences.<ref name=\"Engine Research Laboratory Awards\" /> Prof. Agarwal is a member of the National Committee of the Institution of Engineers (India) for Professional Engineers (PE) Certification in Mechanical Engineering since 2016.\n\nAt IIT Kanpur, Prof. Agarwal is leading the research park initiative as Founder Professor-in-Charge and has established a functional University Research Park, which is responsible for bringing Industry and academia closer. He has established wprld class \"Engine Research Laboratory\" at IIT Kanpur. He has supervised 14 PhD students and 45 Master's students so far. Many of his students are faculty members in other IITs in India, trying to bring Indian IC Engine Research on global map.\n\n== Awards and honors ==\nProf. Agarwal received the Young Scientist Award of the [[Department of Science and Technology (India)|Department of Science and Technology]] in 2002, followed by the Career Award for Young Teachers of the [[All India Council of Technical Education]] (AICTE) in 2004.<ref name=\"ResearchGate profile\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Avinash_Agarwal4/info |title=ResearchGate profile |date=2017 |publisher=ResearchGate}}</ref> The Young Engineer Award of the [[Indian National Academy of Engineering]] was bestowed upon him in 2005<ref name=\"INAE Young Engineer Award\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.csir.res.in/External/Heads/aboutcsir/announcements/young_engineer.html |title=INAE Young Engineer Award |date=2017 |publisher=Council of Scientific and Industrial Research |access-date=12 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323181922/http://www.csir.res.in/External/Heads/aboutcsir/announcements/young_engineer.html |archive-date=23 March 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and the Young Scientists Medal of the [[Indian National Science Academy]] came his way in 2007.<ref name=\"INSA Young Scientists Medal\">{{Cite web |url=http://insaindia.res.in/youngmedal.php |title=INSA Young Scientists Medal |date=2016 |publisher=Indian National Science Academy}}</ref> He received the Alkyl Amine Young Scientist Award of the [[Institute of Chemical Technology]] the same year and a year later, [[SAE International]] selected him for the 2008 Ralph R. Teetor Educational Award.<ref name=\"Ten Engineering Educators Receive SAE Award\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.sae.org/news/830/ |title=Ten Engineering Educators Receive SAE Award |date=7 July 2008 |publisher=SAE International |access-date=12 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170213000556/https://www.sae.org/news/830/ |archive-date=13 February 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He received the C. V. Raman Young Teachers Award of the [[IES Group of Institutions|IES Group]] in 2011 and NASI-[[Reliance Industries]] Platinum Jubilee Award of the [[National Academy of Sciences, India]] in 2012.<ref name=\"NASI-Reliance Industries Platinum Jubilee Award\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nasi.org.in/ripja.htm |title=NASI-Reliance Industries Platinum Jubilee Award |date=2017 |publisher=National Academy of Sciences, India}}</ref> The Indian National Academy of Engineering honored him again in 2012 with the Silver Jubilee Young Engineer Award, which was followed by \"Rajib Goyal Prize\" in Physical Sciences-2015 from Kurukshetra University and then [[Council of Scientific and Industrial Research]] awarded him the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize]], one of the highest Indian science awards in 2016.<ref name=\"Engineering Sciences\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.csir.res.in/external/heads/career/award/BPRIZE/Engineering_SCIENCES.htm |title=Engineering Sciences |date=2016 |publisher=Council of Scientific and Industrial Research |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923211647/http://www.csir.res.in/external/heads/career/award/BPRIZE/Engineering_SCIENCES.htm |archivedate=23 September 2015 }}</ref> Afterwards, he was conferred \"Er. M P Baya National Award-2017\" in Mechanical Engineering by Institution of Engineers, Udaipur and Clarivate Analytics India Research Excellence - Citation Award-2017, which was 6th Edition prize for high citations and high impact work from India, given by Clarivate Analytics, an arm of Web of Science.\n\nProf. Agarwal, who held the BOYSCAST Fellowship of Department of Science and Technology in 2002 and Devendra Shukla Research Fellowship of IIT Kanpur in 2009, was elected as a fellow by the American Association for the Advancement in Science (AAAS) in 2019, and the Indian National Academy of Engineering in 2015.<ref name=\"Agarwal on INAE\" /> He is also an elected fellow of the [[American Society of Mechanical Engineers]] and [[SAE International]], Royal Society of Chemistry, Indian National Academy of Engineering, National Academy of Sciences and International Society for Energy, Environment and Sustainability<ref name=\"Engine Research Laboratory Awards\" /> He was listed in several editions of [[Marquis Who's Who]] in Science and Engineering, Who's Who (Emerging Leaders) and Who's Who in the World.<ref name=\"Engine Research Laboratory Awards\" /> Prof. Agarwal occupied the \"Poonam and Prabhu Goyal Chair\" at IIT Kanpur from 2013\u201316. He is currently 'SBI Endowed chair Professor' in the same institution since 2018 for a period of three years.\n\n== Selected bibliography ==\n=== Books ===\n\n* Simulations and Optical Diagnostics for Internal Combustion Engines Current Status and Way Forward, 163 pages, Published by Springer, Singapore (2020), (Eds.)\u00a0 Akhilendra Pratap Singh, Pravesh Chandra Shukla, Joonsik Hwang, Avinash Kumar Agarwal (ISBN # 978-981-15-0335-1) DOI: 10.1007/978-981-15-0335-1.\n* Advanced Combustion Techniques and Engine Technologies for the Automotive Sector, 256 pages, Published by Springer, Singapore (2020), (Eds.)\u00a0 Akhilendra Pratap Singh, Nikhil Sharma, Ramesh Agarwal, Avinash Kumar Agarwal (ISBN # 978-981-15-0368-9) DOI: 