I: 10.1016/j.fuel.2017.04.016; ISSN # 0016-2361).\n* Akhilendra Pratap Singh, Anuj Pal, Neeraj Kumar Gupta, Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, \u201cParticulate Emissions from Laser Ignited and Spark Ignited Hydrogen Fueled Engines\u201d International Journal of Hydrogen Energy, 42(24), pp 15956-15965, June 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016</sub>: 3.647; DOI: 10.1016/j.ijhydene.2017.04.031; ISSN # 0360-3199).\n* Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, Akhilendra Pratap Singh, Anuj Pal, \u201cEffect of Laser Parameters and Compression Ratio on Particulate Emissions from a Laser Ignited Hydrogen Engine\u201d, International Journal of Hydrogen Energy, 42(15), pp 10622-10635, April 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016</sub>: 3.647; DOI: 10.1016/j.ijhydene.2017.03.074; ISSN # 0360-3199).\n* SMV Sagar, Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, \u201cExperimental Investigation of Varying Composition of HCNG on Performance and Combustion Characteristics of a SI Engine\u201d, International Journal of Hydrogen Energy, 42(18), pp 13234-13244, May 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016</sub>: 3.647; DOI: 10.1016/j.ijhydene.2017.03.063; ISSN # 0360-3199;).\n* Nikhil Sharma, Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, \u201cEffect of Fuel Injection Pressure on Particulate Emissions from a Gasohol (E15 & M15)-Fuelled Gasoline Direct Injection Engine\u201d, Energy and Fuels, 31 (4), pp 4155\u20134164, 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016:</sub> 3.091; DOI: 10.1021/acs.energyfuels.6b02877; ISSN # 0887-0624).\n* Akhilendra P. Singh, Avinash K. Agarwal*, \u201cPartially Homogenous Charge Compression Ignition Engine Development for Low Volatility Fuels\u201d, Energy and Fuels, Vol. 31 (3), pp. 3164\u20133181, 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016:</sub> 3.091; DOI: 10.1021/acs.energyfuels.6b02832; ISSN # 0887-0624).\n* Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, Akhilendra Pratap Singh, Rakesh Kumar Maurya, \u201cEvolution, Challenges and Path Forward for Low Temperature Combustion Engines\u201d, Progress in Energy and Combustion Science, Vol. 61, pp 1-56, July 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016:</sub> 24.055; DOI: 10.1016/j.pecs.2017.02.001; ISSN # 0360-1285).\n* Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, Jaigopal Gupta, Atul Dhar, \"Potential and Challenges for Large Scale Application of Biodiesel in Automotive Sector\", Progress in Energy and Combustion Science, Vol. 61, pp. 113-149, July 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016:</sub> 24.055; DOI: 10.1016/j.pecs.2017.03.002; ISSN # 0360-1285).\n* Akhilendra P. Singh, Avinash K. Agarwal*, \u201cCI/PCCI Combustion Mode Switching of Diesohol Fuelled Production Engine\u201d, SAE 2017-01-0738, SAE Special Publication-2017. (DOI: 10.4271/2017-01-0738).\n* Ayush Jain, Akhilendra P. Singh, Avinash K. Agarwal*, \u201cEffect of Split Fuel Injection and EGR on NOx and PM Emission Reduction in a Low Temperature Combustion (LTC) Mode Diesel Engine\u201d, Energy, Vol. 122, pp. 249-264, March 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016</sub>: 5.182; DOI: 10.1016/j.energy.2017.01.050; ISSN # 0360-5442).\n* Ayush Jain, Akhilendra Pratap Singh, Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, Effect of Fuel Injection Parameters on Combustion Stability and Emissions of a Mineral Diesel Fueled Partially Premixed Charge Compression Ignition (PCCI) Engine, Applied Energy, Vol. 190, pp. 658-669, March 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016</sub>: 7.500; DOI: 10.1016/j.apenergy.2016.12.164; ISSN # 0306-2619).\n* Rajesh Kumar Prasad, Siddhant Jain, Gaurav Verma, Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, \u201cLaser Ignition and Flame Kernel Characterization of HCNG in a Constant Volume Combustion Chamber\u201d, Fuel, Vol. 190, pp. 318-327, February 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016:</sub> 4.726; DOI: 10.1016/j.fuel.2016.11.003; ISSN # 0016-2361).\n* Sanghoon Lee, Chang Sik Lee, Sungwook Park*, Jai Gopal Gupta, Rakesh Kumar Maurya, Avinash Kumar Agarwal, \u201cSpray Characteristics, Engine Performance and Emission Analysis for Karanja Biodiesel and Its Blends\u201d, Energy, Vol. 119, pp. 138-151, January 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016</sub>: 5.182; DOI: 10.1016/j.energy.2016.12.043; ISSN # 0360-5442).\n* Yeshudas Jiotode, Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, Endoscopic Combustion Characterization of Jatropha Biodiesel in a Compression Ignition Engine, Energy, Vol. 119, pp. 845-851, January 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016</sub>: 5.182; DOI: 10.1016/j.energy.2016.11.056; ISSN # 0360-5442).\n* Pravesh Chandra Shukla, Tarun Gupta, Nitin Kumar Labhsetwar, Rohini Khobragade, Neeraj Gupta, and Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, \u201cEffectiveness of Non-Noble Metal Based Diesel Oxidation Catalysts on Particle Number Emissions from Diesel and Biodiesel Exhaust\u201d, Science of Total Environment (STOTEN), Vol. 574, pp. 1512-1520, January 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016:</sub> 5.102; DOI: <nowiki>http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.scitotenv.2016.08.155</nowiki>; ISSN # 0048-9697).\n* Pravesh Chandra Shukla, Tarun Gupta, Nitin Kumar Labhsetwar and Avinash Kumar Agarwal*, \u201cTrace Metals and Ions in Particulates Emitted by Biodiesel Fuelled Engine\u201d, Fuel, Vol. 188, pp. 603-609, January 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016:</sub> 4.726; DOI: <nowiki>http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.fuel.2016.10.059</nowiki>; ISSN # 0016-2361).\n* Vikram Kumar, Sujeet Kumar Sinha*, Avinash Kumar Agarwal, \u201cTribological Studies of Epoxy Composites with Solid and Liquid Fillers\u201d, Tribology International, Vol. 105, pp. 27-36, January 2017. (Impact Factor<sub>2016:</sub> 2.971; DOI: <nowiki>http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.triboint.2016.09.010</nowiki>; ISSN # 0301-679X).\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Diesel fuel]]\n* [[Vegetable oil]]\n{{portal|India|Engineering}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{Cite web |last= Avinash Kumar Agrawal|url=http://www.eprint.iitd.ac.in/bitstream/2074/6452/1/TH-2661.pdf |title=Performance evaluation and tribological studies on a biodiesel-fuelled compression ignition engine |date=1996 |publisher=IIT Delhi |work=Doctoral thesis}}\n* {{Cite web |title=Alternative Fuels |last=Avinash K. Agarwal |publisher=Proceedings of the Institution of Mechanical Engineers, Part D volume 221 